"title": "6175: guilt, removal of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6175: guilt, removal of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Through the death of Jesus Christ, God has provided a means of removing guilt, thus opening the way for believers to know the blessings of a right relationship with him.</p>\n<h2>The removal of guilt is God's work</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:22\">JER 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:20\">JER 50:20</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:33\">ROM 8:33</a></strong> <em>“Justify” is a legal term which includes the meaning “to declare not guilty”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:8\">1CH 21:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:1-Ps32:5\">PSA 32:1–32:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1-Isa6:6\">ISA 6:1–6:6</a></p>\n<h2>The removal of guilt requires confession</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:5\">PSA 32:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:10\">2SA 24:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:8\">1CH 21:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:14\">PSA 51:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:12-Jer3:13\">JER 3:12–3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:21\">ACT 11:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:25\">2TI 2:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:8-1John1:9\">1JN 1:8–1:9</a></p>\n<h2>The removal of guilt by the OT sacrificial system</h2>\n<h3>Guilt removed by the guilt offering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:6-Lev6:7\">LEV 6:6–6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:20-Lev19:22\">LEV 19:20–19:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:18-Ezra10:19\">EZR 10:18–10:19</a></p>\n<h3>Guilt removed by the sin offering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:27-Num15:28\">NUM 15:27–15:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:5-Lev5:6\">LEV 5:5–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:9-Num6:11\">NUM 6:9–6:11</a></p>\n<h3>Guilt removed by the Day of Atonement</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:20-Lev16:34\">LEV 16:20–16:34</a></p>\n<h3>Animal sacrifices are ultimately ineffective in removing guilt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:1-Heb10:4\">HEB 10:1–10:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:9\">HEB 9:9</a></p>\n<h2>The removal of guilt by Jesus Christ's sacrificial death</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10-Isa53:12\">ISA 53:10–53:12</a></strong> <em>This prophecy finds its ultimate fulfilment in the person of Jesus Christ</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a> <em>The point of John's image is that Jesus Christ will be sacrificed, as lambs were, to remove people's guilt</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:9\">ROM 5:9</a> <em>The blood of Jesus Christ referred to here is his shed blood, and therefore speaks of his (sacrificial) death</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a> <em>Human guilt is transferred to Jesus Christ, in order that believers might become righteous before God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:11-Heb10:14\">HEB 10:11–10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>The results of guilt being removed</h2>\n<h3>A clean conscience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:22\">HEB 10:22</a></p>\n<h3>Peace with God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:5\">ISA 53:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1\">ROM 5:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19-Col1:20\">COL 1:19–1:20</a></p>\n<h3>Access into God's presence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1-Rom5:2\">ROM 5:1–5:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:18\">EPH 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Joy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:1-Ps32:11\">PSA 32:1–32:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1-Rom5:2\">ROM 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h3>Hope</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:1-Rom5:2\">ROM 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h3>A desire to worship God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:14-Ps51:15\">PSA 51:14–51:15</a></p>\n<h3>A desire to serve God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:6-Isa6:8\">ISA 6:6–6:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15-John21:20\">JHN 21:15–21:20</a></p>",
